  "$comment": "F1 world championship scoring rules per season, 1950-2026. Authored from the project research digest (docs/research/RESEARCH.md section 4); validated by replaying f1db raw results through the points engine and asserting equality with official standings. Constructors dropped-score rules for 1958-1980 are the least-documented area and are expected to be corrected by oracle iteration - see $oracleNotes.",
  "$oracleNotes": [
    "ORACLE-VERIFIED (first full run, 2026-07-02): constructors.bestN='sameAsDrivers' holds for 1958-1978 (except the 1961 table quirk below); best-car-only ended after 1978 - 1979 already scored every car (Ferrari 113 = 60+53), so 1979 is bestCarOnly=false.",
    "1961: the constructors cup stayed on the old 8-6-4-3-2-1 win-8 scale while drivers moved to 9-6-4-3-2-1 (Ferrari 40 = 5 best-car wins x 8). Expressed via constructors.racePoints.",
    "Half-points rounds are authored as roundOverrides with pointsFactor 1/2: 1975 Spain, 1975 Austria, 1984 Monaco, 1991 Australia, 2009 Malaysia, 2021 Belgium. 2014 Abu Dhabi double points is pointsFactor 2. The factor scales race-session points only; sprints always paid in full.",
    "Indianapolis 500 counted for the drivers championship 1950-1960 but never for constructors (which exists only from 1958): roundOverrides 1958-1960.",
    "1997: Michael Schumacher excluded from the drivers classification, results stand (points kept, no position). Excluded CONSTRUCTORS (2007 McLaren spygate, 2018 pre-split Force India) lose their points entirely - different official semantics, both modeled.",
    "pointsAdjustments carry documented flat corrections raw results cannot express: constructors-only penalties (1995/2000/2020) and 1950s shared-drive stewards' allocations (1953/1956/1957).",
    "Entry-level eligibility (F2 cars in the 1958-69 German GPs, unregistered second cars 1984 Monza / 1987 Adelaide, Hill's annulled 1963 French GP podium) is derived by the fixture generator from f1db's per-row race_points and carried as pointsEligible/pointsPosition flags - not authored here."
  ],
